findings.subquery: background and biography of Tarun Manohar Jaswani
key_findings: Tarun Manohar Jaswani is an Indian entrepreneur and business executive born on June 27, 1977, in Delhi, India.
He is the son of Manohar Khemchand Jaswani, a prominent businessman.

Tarun holds a Bachelor of Technology in Engineering from the Department of Technology, Savitribai Phule Pune University, and the Maharashtra Academy of Engineering and Educational Research Maharashtra Institute of Technology, Kothrud, Pune.
He began his professional career as a Project Trainee at Tata Motors, working on the TATA Indica project.
He later served as a Network Engineer at BPL Telecom, focusing on call monitoring and call drop algorithms.

In December 2001, Tarun co-founded Ring India Infotech Private Limited, a network of third-party international call centers in the Asia Pacific region, offering customized voice and web-based services to clients in the US, Europe, and Australia.
In July 2001, he co-founded Interfacemax Contacts Private Limited, an investment fund focused on blockchain opportunities and initiatives, including smart contracts and algorithmic trading.
In August 2014, he became an Additional Director at Maravilloso Realtors Private Limited, a real estate company based in Delhi, India.
Tarun is also the Founder and Chief Executive Officer of Unbound Finance, a financial software company.
He has been involved in various ventures, including virtual reality ad serving technologies and programmatic digital media buys.
He has a strong background in blockchain technology, smart contracts, and algorithmic trading.
